sentences: Celius Hudson Dougherty (May 27, 1902 – December 22, 1986) was an American pianist and composer of art songs and other music.
He claimed that he wrote his first song when he was seven years old.
In 1924 he won the "Schubert Prize" for piano performance, sponsored by the Schubert Club.
In New York, where he lived for nearly fifty years, he performed his piano Sonata in E Flat at Aeolian Hall in 1925 and his Sonata for Violin and Piano in 1930.
